1.text: Saturate a cotton pad in isopropyl alcohol.

2.text: Wipe the cotton pad over the handle of your brush.
2.vid: /7/7d/Clean Gel Nail Polish Brushes Step 2 Version 2.360p.mp4

3.text: Set the cotton pad down and wipe the bristles on it.
3.vid: /9/9a/Clean Gel Nail Polish Brushes Step 3 Version 2.360p.mp4

4.text: Add clear nail gel to your brush if you are having trouble getting the color out.
4.vid: /b/b3/Clean Gel Nail Polish Brushes Step 4 Version 2.360p.mp4

5.text: Wipe your brush back and forth over the cotton pad.
5.vid: /5/56/Clean Gel Nail Polish Brushes Step 5 Version 2.360p.mp4

6.text: Brush the excess gel onto a towel after each use.

7.text: Wipe the bristles with a lint-free cloth after you use them.
7.vid: /c/c7/Clean Gel Nail Polish Brushes Step 7 Version 2.360p.mp4

8.text: Get any stickiness off the handle with isopropyl alcohol.
8.vid: /4/43/Clean Gel Nail Polish Brushes Step 8 Version 2.360p.mp4

9.text: Keep your brush away from UV light.
